docs.snippet: MEXICO CITY, Nov. 10-- Although sand in one eye blurred his vision, Arnold Palmer assumed the individual lead in the World Cup golf matches today with a twounder-par 70 for 138. Jack Nicklaus had a 71 and the United States team widened its advantage...
docs.lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY, Nov. 10-- Although sand in one eye blurred his vision, Arnold Palmer assumed the individual lead in the World Cup golf matches today with a twounder-par 70 for 138. Jack Nicklaus had a 71 and the United States team widened its advantage to six strokes with a 36-hole aggregate of 281.

headline.main: PALMER SETS PACE WITH A 70 FOR 138; Plays 2-Under-Par Round Despite Sand its an Eye --Nicklaus Shoots 71

docs.lead_paragraph: IT has no place on the Great Society's list of priorities. It's not a subject most Americans want to think about, much less discuss. Yet some 4-million men in the United States live in fear and trembling over it. They are homosexuals. They want freedom of sex.
docs.abstract: W Schott article on problems confronting 4-million homosexuals in US; notes changes in sex attitudes but absence of any changes in sex laws; discusses homosexuals demands for total freedom, speculates on possibility of their realization; points up rising number of groups concerned with problem; illus

headline.main: Civil Rights and the Homosexual A 4-Million Minority Asks for Equal Rights; 4-Million Minority (Cont.) Some sex-law reformers are asking for the moon

docs.snippet: LA PAZ, Bolivia, Nov. 14 The plan of Ernesto Che Guevara to create a "second Vietnam" in the heart of South America emerges clearly in captured documents that have been made public here at the trial of Regis Debray.
docs.lead_paragraph: LA PAZ, Bolivia, Nov. 14 The plan of Ernesto Che Guevara to create a "second Vietnam" in the heart of South America emerges clearly in captured documents that have been made public here at the trial of Regis Debray.
docs.abstract: diary, other seized documents reveal Guevara's plan to create '2d Vietnam' aided and supported by Cuba; Debray seen high-level courier between Guevara and Castro; Guevara role detailed; Cuba apparently unable to agree with Bolivian Communist party on party aid to guerrillas; reptdly urged ex-Vice Pres Lechin to ask supporters to join band; ex-Pres Paz Estenssoro, exiled in Peru, reptdly sought to organize 2d guerrilla front on Brazil border

headline.main: Guevara Documents Detail Plan for '2d Vietnam'

byline.original: By JUAN de ONIS Special to The New York Times

docs.snippet: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay--A devaluation of the peso in Uruguay Nov. 6 has caused a rush to cash in hoarded dollars. But the drastic economic move is also inspiring a cautious optimism over the country's economic future.
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay--A devaluation of the peso in Uruguay Nov. 6 has caused a rush to cash in hoarded dollars. But the drastic economic move is also inspiring a cautious optimism over the country's economic future.
docs.abstract: Nov 6 devaluation credited with spurring other reforms and econ activity; peso now at 198-200 to $1

headline.main: URUGUAY HELPED BY DEVALUATION; Economic Activity Picks Up in Wake of Drastic Action
